<emphasis id="E3ED26401B08FFC4FD76F463FCEEF7F3" bold="true" box="[738,894,2066,2095]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B08FFC4FC37F463FCB8F789" authority="Thomas" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1918" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pontifex">Ctenomys pontifex Thomas, 1918</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B08FFC4FCA2F445FB87F728" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388304" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">“East side of the Andes near Fort San Rafael, Province of Mendoza.” Restricted by O. P. Pearson and H. A. Lagiglia in 1992 to “Volcan Peteroa, Malargtie department, ca. 35°26’S, 70°20°'W.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B08FFC4FD73F488FCBCF64E" blockId="22.[738,1333,2066,2488]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B08FFC4FD73F488FC41F6C6" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1918" box="[743,977,2297,2330]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pontifex">Ctenomys pontifex</taxonomicName>
is not classified in any species group. Karyotype is 2n = 50, and sperm form remains unknown. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
